-- Swiss attorney general brings charges in HSBC Swiss bank case
-- By Joshua Franklin
-- Thu Dec 11, 2014 04:54AM EST
-- None



ZURICH, Dec 11 (Reuters) - Switzerland's attorney general said on Thursday it had brought charges against a former computer technical analyst at HSBC's <HSBA.L> private bank in Geneva, who is suspected of having shopped confidential client data to foreign authorities.

"The fugitive IT specialist is suspected of having proposed computerized data to Lebanese banks as well as to several foreign authorities," the Office of the Attorney General of Switzerland said in a statement. The prosecutor did not name the employee.